1. Definitions

"Software" means Caramel Board and all files provided in this repository,
including source code, documentation, build scripts, user interface assets,
icons, logos, application packaging, desktop launchers, server components, and
client components.

"Built Desktop Application" means any compiled, bundled, packaged, or
installable desktop version of the Software, including app bundles, installers,
MSI packages, DMG packages, EXE installers, portable executable packages, and
packages that include bundled server, client, runtime, or resource files.

"Third Party" means any person or legal entity outside you or your organization.
If you are an individual, "your organization" means only you. If you are using
the Software on behalf of a company, studio, school, or other organization, it
means that organization and its employees or contractors acting for internal
purposes.

"Internal Use" means use by you or your organization for your own personal,
business, research, creative, educational, or operational purposes, where the
Software is not provided to a Third Party as a product, service, hosted service,
managed service, bundled application, or deliverable.

"Third-Party Components" means dependencies, runtimes, libraries, tools, fonts,
models, datasets, and other components that are not owned by the Caramel Board
project and are included with, linked from, documented for, or used by the
Software.

